HEADWORD: Putrescin
<hw>Pu*tres"cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A nontoxic diamine, <chform>C4H12N2</chform>, formed
in the putrefaction of the flesh of mammals and some other
animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Putrid</ent>⟦br⟧
